{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"extrovert-dippy-bongo","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\n13 Jira issues are pinned at Jira's 5000-comment HARD cap, inflated by the pre-P1\nnon-idempotent re-posting bug (local truth 22-76 distinct comments each; Jira has ~65 copies\nof each until 5000). P1 (landed a6cdad0e2) STOPS new duplication, but the caps remain — so\nNEW comments on these 13 tickets still silently fail to sync until the duplicates are purged.\nRequires purging ~4900+ duplicate comments per ticket in Jira.\n\nThe 13 issues (rebar-id -> Jira key, local-distinct/Jira-total):\nREB-155(5fd2, 76/5000) REB-352(e0e2,64) REB-428(8937,31) REB-341(db7b,30) REB-289(b744,29)\nREB-427(822a,27) REB-183(7284,25) REB-327(d251,25) REB-424(2359,25) REB-425(33d0,25)\nREB-190(75a9,22) REB-426(59ef,22) REB-453(b4d4,22).\n\n## Sequencing (CRITICAL)\n\nRun ONLY after P1 is live in the reconciler (the reconcile-bridge installs from main each run,\nso P1 reaches it within minutes of landing — confirm via a green reconcile-bridge run on a\npost-a6cdad0e2 commit). Else the (pre-P1) reconciler re-inflates within minutes.\n\n## What — irreversible; execute under the T4 safety plan\n\n- [ ] Backup: export FULL comment payload (id, body, author, created) for all 13 tickets to a\n      versioned JSON artifact BEFORE any deletion.\n- [ ] Keep-one dedup: for each distinct normalized body, keep the OLDEST (lowest created),\n      delete the rest; NEVER delete a body with only one copy; only delete bridge-bot-authored\n      comments (never human comments). Jira REST DELETE /rest/api/3/issue/{key}/comment/{id}.\n- [ ] Dry-run FIRST: emit the exact per-ticket delete list (comment ids + kept canonical) and\n      show the diff for human approval before --execute.\n- [ ] Idempotent + resumable; log each deletion (ticket, comment id, body hash).\n- [ ] Auth: JIRA_API_TOKEN in env; acli authenticated to navasage.atlassian.net (project REB).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Backup artifact + dry-run diff produced and human-approved BEFORE deletion.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The 13 tickets are below the 5000 cap after cleanup; a subsequent\n      reconcile pass posts a new comment to one of them successfully (proves sync restored).\n- [ ] Deletion log artifact retained.","id":"bd80-0603-7d44-4d9f","parent_id":"58b0-104b-777c-4227","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Jira data cleanup: purge duplicate comments on the 13 capped tickets (after P1 deploys; dry-run+approval first)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784340046317331001,"uuid":"4eae02ba-5727-4b21-81b0-9e35b7171fc1"}